text.section:
Each operator shall notify the Bureau immediately in the manner the Bureau prescribes if:
Any change occurs in the name of the operator of a mine, an executive official concerned with its operation, or in the designation of the mine;
A mine has been abandoned or work discontinued;
Work has commenced for the purpose of opening a new mine. The notice shall include sketch maps outlining the plans intended to be pursued in the opening;
The working of a mine is resumed after an abandonment or discontinuance for a period exceeding two months; or
A squeeze, crush, or fire occurs, or a dangerous body of water, explosive, or noxious gas is found.
